Subject: Re: [T2] How to tell if a cv is bad

On Wed, 30 Apr 2003 sethmatteson(-at-)att.net wrote:

> I got one of my cv joints all cleaned up and it looks like there is some slight
> pitting of the center hub where the bearings ride. Is this cv joint trash or
> can I continue to use it?

Minor pitting isn't a problem.  It's when balls and races start to show
serious galling that replacement is a good idea.  I've put CVs with minor
pitting back in and had good life out of them.

George Lyle
